{"lemma":"نَقْضُ","slug":"نَقْضُ","root":"ن.ق.ض","root_slug":"ن-ق-ض","root_link":"/words/roots/ن-ق-ض","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"نَقْض","root":"نقض","pos":"N","occurrence_count":2},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["","n40429","n40430","n40431"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%86%D9%8E%D9%82%D9%92%D8%B6%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to break, to demolish"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to break (a treaty, covenant, promise, etc), to renege","examples":[{"text":"ٱلَّذِينَ يَنقُضُونَ عَهْدَ ٱللَّهِ مِن بَعْدِ مِيثَـٰقِهِ وَيَقْطَعُونَ مَآ أَمَرَ ٱللَّهُ بِهِ أَن يُوصَلَ وَيُفْسِدُونَ فِى ٱلْأَرْضِ أُو۟لَـٰٓئِكَ هُمُ ٱلْخَـٰسِرُونَ","english":"those who violate Allah’s covenant after it has been affirmed, break whatever ˹ties˺ Allah has ordered to be maintained, and spread corruption in the land. It is they who are the ˹true˺ losers."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to veto, to repeal"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to peel off","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to cut, to split, to slit open, to crack"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Morphologically from the root ن ق ض (n q ḍ).\n\nSee the etymology of the corresponding lemma form."},"ipa":["/na.qa.dˤa/","/naq.qa.dˤa/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n40429","headword_ar":"نُقْضٌ","root":"nqD","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"niqoDN","text_ar":"نِقْضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n40430","headword_ar":"نِقْضٌ","root":"nqD","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manoquwDN","text_ar":"مَنْقُوضٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Undone; taken,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pulled, to pieces: untwisted: unravelled: unwoven: dissolved; broken:"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c. (see 1:)] (S, Mgh, Msb, K:) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nikovN","text_ar":"نِكْثٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA) in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manokuwvN","text_ar":"مَنْكُوثٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuqoDN","text_ar":"نُقْضٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Mgh, Msb;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naqaDN","text_ar":"نَقَضٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Sgh:) but El-Ghooree allows only the first: (Mgh:) Az, however, mentions only the second; (Msb;) which signifies as above, applied to a building, or structure; (M, Mgh;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what has become taken,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pulled, to pieces,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA A@notaqaDa","text_ar":"مَا ا@نْتَقَضَ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a building,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"structure;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) as also the first: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naqoDN","text_ar":"نَقْضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA naqaDota","text_ar":"مَا نَقَضْتَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what thou hast undone; taken,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pulled, to pieces; untwisted;"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]: (M:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is undone, of"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the stuff of the tents called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axobiyap","text_ar":"اَخْبِيَة"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and of"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the garments called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akosiyap","text_ar":"اَكْسِيَة"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and twisted a second time;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naqaDN","text_ar":"نَقَضٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuqaADapN","text_ar":"نُقَاضَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (L:) or this last signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is undone of a hair-rope:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K:) the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"niqoDN","text_ar":"نِقْضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anoqaADN","text_ar":"اَنْقَاضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a pl. of pauc.], (M,) and of the same, (Msb,) or of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuqoDN","text_ar":"نُقْضٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, Msb,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuquwDN","text_ar":"نُقُوضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Mgh, Msb.) ―         -b2-  (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Emaciated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rendered lean,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by travel;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon which one has journeyed time after time:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O:) Seer says,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as though travel had unknit its frame;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA;) thus indicating it to be tropical: (TA:) applied to a male camel, (S, M, K,) and to a horse, (M.) and to a female camel, (S, K,) or the female is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"niqoDapN","text_ar":"نِقْضَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M, K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anoqaADN","text_ar":"اَنْقَاضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Sb, S, K,) only, (Sb, M,) both of the masc. and fem.; in the latter, the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"being imagined to be elided; (M;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naqaAy^iDu","text_ar":"نَقَايِضُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is [also said to be] a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"niqoDN","text_ar":"نِقْضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"jaded,"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to a she-camel. (So in a copy of the S in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nfS","text_ar":"نفص"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b3-  [See an ex. in a verse cited voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sad~N","text_ar":"سَدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b4-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"place,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"crust of earth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K,) that becomes broken from over truffles; (S, M, K;) for when they are about to come"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2844},{"kind":"text","text":"forth, they break asunder the surface of the earth: (O:) pl. [of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anoqaADN","text_ar":"اَنْقَاضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuquwDN","text_ar":"نُقُوضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M, K.) ―         -b5-  Accord. to the K,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nifoDN","text_ar":"نِفْضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but the latter is a mistranscription; (TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Honey that has in it"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"worms of the kind called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suws","text_ar":"سُوس"},{"kind":"text","text":";"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wherefore it is taken,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nfD","text_ar":"نفض"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and pounded,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, ubi supra,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the place of the bees is smeared"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yulaT~axu","text_ar":"يُلَطَّخُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in a copy of the M"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yuTobaxu","text_ar":"يُطْبَخُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is doubtless a mistranscription,])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"therewith, together with myrtle"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=s","text_ar":"ا=س"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the bees then come to it, and deposit their honey in it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K, ubi supra;) on the authority of El-Hejeree: (M:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dung of bees in the place where they deposit their honey:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, AHn, K, ubi supra:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bees that have died therein."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sgh, K, ubi supra.)       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naqiyDN","text_ar":"نَقِيضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["S","Mgh","Msb","K","TA","Sgh","M","L","O","Sb"]},{"entry_id":"n40431","headword_ar":"نَقَضٌ","root":"nqD","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"niqoDN","text_ar":"نِقْضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places."}],"source_refs":[]}]}}